{
  "text": "Here is an outline of this paper. In Section 2, we give a review on Artin-Schreier theory and some results of [CITATION_1] about the relationship between irreducible strata of AS g and partitions of integers. Section 3 introduces some deformation results and gives us information on how irreducible strata fit together in AS g by looking at their corresponding partitions (Theorem 3.7). Open Question 1 of [CITATION_2] is also answered in this section. Connectedness of AS g is discussed in Section 4. In particular, Theorem 1.1 will be proved in this section using Theorem 3.7 and graph theory on the \"tree\" formed by partitions of d. The details of how the deformations are constructed are postponed to Section 5, which is the most novel part, but also the most technical part of this paper.",
